  "unmapped_findings": [
    "The 35 h milled powder exhibited thermal stability up to ~500 °C; Fe5Si3-type silicide phase formed at ~520 °C upon annealing, as confirmed by ex-situ XRD after annealing at 600 °C and 800 °C.",
    "The SPSed sample achieved an ultimate compressive strength of ~2046 ± 160 MPa and a compressive ductility of ~19% at room temperature and strain rate of 10^-3 s^-1; the measured yield stress under compression was also reported as 2046 ± 160 MPa.",
    "Dominant strengthening mechanisms in the SPSed sample were grain-boundary strengthening (~52.55%) and dislocation strengthening (~30.00%), with minor contributions from precipitation (~5.70%) and solid solution strengthening (~6.14%); theoretical total yield stress ~2164 MPa.",
    "Fig. 9(e and f) show comparative microhardness versus density and ultimate compressive stress versus density plots benchmarking the present alloy against conventional stainless steels, dual-phase steels, and various reported HEAs.",
    "Annealing of 35 h milled powder at 400 °C and 500 °C retained the BCC + γ-brass + B2 phase assemblage, while annealing at 800 °C increased the B2 phase fraction (~40%) and coarsened the Fe5Si3-type silicide.",
    "The SPSed sample had a relative density of ~99% with experimental density ~6.49 ± 0.3 g/cm³ (theoretical density 6.55 g/cm³ by rule of mixture)."
  ]
}